<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-10T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">761.94/629a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="to">Grew</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-10T12:00:00-05:00">October 10,
                                1933—noon</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. What significance do you attach to statement reportedly made
                            yesterday by War Office spokesman to Associated Press correspondent
                            concerning possible Japanese demand on Russia for “amends, retraction,
                            and guarantee of future good faith. Otherwise stronger measures may be
                            necessary.”?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>